Program: Discovery
Title: Rats - a special report
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrwvf
Last Broadcast Date: 18 March 1997
Programme about rats. The rodents often strike fear into humans who will feel disgust when they see a rat. But as being kept as pets, rats have also been eaten as a delicacy in the past. Their connection with the spread of the plague in the 1600s however set the precedence for their reputation as disease-carrying vermin. Show less